<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PIVOTAL CALL SINKS LAKERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD _ It figured to come down like this. Dennis Rodman
reappears, hustles his rear off, displays the demeanor of a choir
boy, and he (begin ital)still(end ital) manages to figure in the
most controversial play of the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   But even the most ardent Worm-a-phobes can't pin that pivotal
play, or Sunday's 113-109 Laker loss to Seattle, on Rodman.
</P>
<P>
   Midway through the fourth quarter, Rodman and Shaquille O'Neal
knocked themselves to the floor wrestling for the same rebound,
with Seattle's Olden Polynice and the Lakers' Tyronn Lue charging
to the pile.
</P>
<P>
   Officials called a jump ball. But not for Rodman, nor O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
   It was 7-foot Polynice vs. 6-foot-in-high-heels Lue.
</P>
<P>
   And it was almost comical. Just not to the Lakers, who watched
Seattle win the tip, get a 3-pointer from Hersey Hawkins and a
fourth point when Hawkins drained the technical foul called against
coach Kurt Rambis.
</P>
<P>
   Within seconds, a tie game became a four-point deficit. Within
minutes it grew to eight points, and several comeback tries later,
it was just another costly, frustrating loss on the home court.
</P>
<P>
   One controversial call, one badly played third quarter, several
breakdowns in final minutes. Nothing new for the Lakers, who can
broad jump 10-foot hurdles only to trip over grains of sand.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's very disappointing,'' O'Neal said. ``I've been saying the
same thing the last two years: We have to play smart, play
consistent. Whenever we lose games like this, it's not because the
other team beat us, it's just because we beat ourselves. Until we
learn how to overcome those silly mistakes in the third and fourth
quarter, we're not going to go anywhere.''
</P>
<P>
   They did maintain footing, however, holding onto fourth place in
the Western Conference thanks to Houston's loss to Utah. But the
Lakers' disjointed play down the stretch doesn't bode well for road
games this week at Portland and Salt Lake City.
</P>
<P>
   Despite everything, they somehow cut Seattle's lead to three
points with 31.3 seconds left. But Robert Horry threw away a pair
of inbounds passes for turnovers, the Sonics hit most of their free
throws, and the Lakers' last-gasp efforts came up short as
Seattle's lead bulged to nine points.
</P>
<P>
   A three-point play from O'Neal and 3-point jumpers by Horry and
Derek Fisher eventually cut the deficit to two points, but with 5.2
seconds left, it was too late.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a hard-fought game,'' Rambis said. ``They played well,
I thought we did a lot of good things. But they just played a
little bit better than us today.''
</P>
<P>
   The jump-ball call just made it harder to stomach.
</P>
<P>
   ``You saw what happened, they made a (bleeped)-up call, like
they always do,'' O'Neal said. ``It was me and Dennis fighting for
the ball, and Ty Lue came from the back after the fact. They was
trying to be cute on the (bleeping) call. You know what happened.
But they (officials) don't get fined by the league.''
</P>
<P>
   Rambis pleaded guilty to an ill-timed technical but added, ``It
was clearly the wrong call. Shaq should have had (the jump
ball).... Ty came in there unbelievably late.''
</P>
<P>
   Kobe Bryant admitted it was ``a tough blow,'' but added, ``You
just have to fight through it.''
</P>
<P>
   It didn't help that the Lakers couldn't slow Gary Payton (33
points) and Vin Baker (20 points). They scored 11 points each in
the third quarter, as the Sonics turned a six-point deficit into an
11-point lead.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers wasted a 50 percent shooting effort and a 25-point,
nine-assist, zero-turnover performance from Bryant. They've also
wasted a string of home games, having gone 2-3 this month, with
only four Forum dates left in the final 11 games.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's looking backwards; I don't do that,'' Rambis said.
``We've just gotta do things to make us better. We did a lot of
good things today. I'm happy with the good things and disappointed
in some other things. We'll watch the videotape and try to learn
from our mistakes.'' &UR; !dlim!!end! &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
