rest at the end of the driveway in a big brown roll. It looked like
a cheap stogy tossed away as unsmokable by a discerning giant. But
this was not just any old, smelly carpet. This was The Last Shag
Carpet in America. Its removal after a quarter-century of wear
marks an end of an era. To dispose it, I didn't know whether to
alert the Smithsonian or the EPA. (Lane, Daytona Beach
News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
