 &HT;    Colorado ranch roundup
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Check out Kids Farm at www.kidsfarm.com to learn about
the animals and people on ranches in Colorado. There are sounds and
scenes of Rocky Mountain farm animals, including horses, cattle,
dogs, sheep, ducks, turkeys and llamas. Click the link to see
photographs and descriptions of the animals, plus a sound sampling.
There are explanations of what grows on the ranch, the equipment
used and rodeos. This fun field trip includes everything but the
smell of the farm animals.
</P>
<P>
   What do you think?
</P>
<P>
   For the past few weeks, you've read about the war in Yugoslavia.
We've told you how the United States and its allies have been
bombing the Serbs to bring peace to the area. Now, we want to know
what you think. Should America be involved there? How do you think
it would feel to be a Kosovar Albanian? What would you do if you
had to leave your home because you were being threatened? Please
write to us at nfk(at)ajc.com. Include your name, grade, school and
phone number. We may call you to be in a story.
</P>
<P>
   Go Daddy-O
</P>
<P>
   Tired of listening to your kid brother's Barney CD while
traveling in the car? Well, there may be a CD for the whole family.
Walt Brewer and John Boydston, both of Atlanta, combine kid
favorites with surf music that your parents will probably like. Bop
down the freeway to ``Scooby Doo, Where Are You?'' or learn new
songs such as ``Ants in My Pants.'' You can sample music from
``Cool Songs for Cool Kids'' at www.daddyagogo.com.
</P>
