<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH PAGE 0409 -- A new twist on an old technology is
being used to create human-like guides to Web sites. Chatterbots
are programs fueled by artificial intelligence software, which has
been around since the 1970s but never found a practical use.
(Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes four 2-column
color photos of a woman using chaterbox technology.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: NET WATCH -- Just as TV can bring graphic depictions of
war and its aftermath to people around the world, the Internet can
provide breadth and depth of content regarding the conflict in
Kosovo. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes a
1-column color photo of refugees in a camp near the Macedonian
border.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECH NOTES -- Are you in the market for a $2.5 million,
single-engine turboprop but just don't have the time to shop? A Web
site, www.buythebest.com, might be worth checking out. The site is
devoted to the real expensive and mildly practical. (Clothier,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes 2-column color photo of
web site www.buythebest.com.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: TECHNOBUDDY -- The Internet and the computer world are
being bombarded regularly by meteor showers when it comes to
viruses and other malicious programs designed to invade your
privacy or destroy information on your hard disk. You need to know
how to defend yourself against such attacks. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) Art includes 1 column color sig of
columnist.
</P>
<P>
   (Eds: This layout is available Tuesday after 2 p.m. EDT)
</P>
