<P>
   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-ATROCITIES (Skopje, Macedonia) _ The immediate needs of
the Kosovo refugees means that war crimes investigators are running
out of time for documenting atrocities. By Charles M. Sennott and
Anne E. Kornblut. 1800 words.
</P>
<P>
   BALKANS-DURATION (Cambridge, Mass.) _ How long can things go on?
The political coalition behind NATO is shaky, with dissent rising
in Germany and deep ambivalence in Italy and Greece. By John Yemma.
1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   BALKANS-VOICES (Undated) _ The Internet has become a virtual
