   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ As the Thursday deadline approaches
for filing 1998 income tax returns, public fervor for tax cuts
seems to be missing. Republicans who have been planning to campaign
for a broad tax cut haven't given up on it, but they are being
forced to talk about other issues. By MARIANNE MEANS.
