<HEADLINE>
NORTON LIGHTS UP `HISTORY'; `LIFE' MIXES KAFKA, CAPRA 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``American History X'' _ Edward Norton's fiery
performance as a skinhead electrifies this complex, tough-minded
story of racism and fascism. It's rough sledding and not as
perceptive as it should be, but it's worth renting.
</P>
<P>
   ``Franz Kafka's It's a Wonderful Life'' _ This short, which is
joined by three others, won the 1995 Academy Award for best
live-action short subject. It's a marvelous mix of Kafka's literary
paranoia and Capra's unadulterated optimism, and stars Richard E.
Grant.
</P>
<P>
   ``Meet Joe Black'' _ This is the movie that may force Anthony
Hopkins into premature retirement. It's such a bloated story it
requires two cassettes. Not even the craze for everything angel _
heck, not even a renewed clamor for Brad Pitt _ could justify this
dumb movie about money and spirituality.
</P>
<P>
   ``A Soldier's Daughter Never Cries'' _ The Merchant-Ivory
production suffers from the failure to make author James Jones the
main character in this semi-autobiographical work. Other than that,
it's a terrific film about families, both touching and intelligent.
</P>
<P>
   ``Beloved'' _ Director Jonathan Demme tries hard to bring an
element of surprise to his adaptation of Toni Morrison's novel. But
it's to no avail. While the performances are fine, including Oprah
Winfrey's in the leading role, the predictability of the tragic
story of slavery undercuts the dramatic impact.
</P>
<P>
   ``Legalese'' _ James Garner stars in the caustic HBO movie about
lawyers and the media manipulating each other. The engaging plot
and terse performances make this one of the best cable-to-video
movies of the year.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: April 13: ``Basil,'' ``One Tough Cop,''
``The Fury Within,'' ``Detroit 9000,'' ``Scooby-Doo's Greatest
Mysteries,'' ``Conspirators of Pleasure.'' April 20: ``A Bug's
Life,'' ``Monument Ave.,'' ``Simon Birch,'' ``Corporate Ladder,''
``Kissed,'' ``Apt Pupil,'' ``A Night at the Roxbury.'' April 27:
``Elizabeth,'' ``Ten Benny,'' ``Stepmom,'' ``Life of Jesus,''
``Happiness,'' ``Ground Control,'' ``The Thief,'' ``Twists of
Terror,'' ``Implicated,'' ``Striking Poses,'' ``Future Fantastic,''
``Streetwise,'' ``At First Sight.'' May 4: ``Babe: Pig in the
City,'' ``You've Got Mail,'' ``The Leather Boys,'' ``Frank Sinatra:
The Best Is Yet to Come.'' May 5: ``Gloria.'' May 11: ``Star Trek:
Insurrection,'' ``Another Day in Paradise,'' ``Velvet Goldmine,''
``As Time Goes By'' (BBC), ``Teletubbies Favorite Things,''
``Orgazmo.'' May 18: ``Holy Man,'' ``The Hanging Garden,''
``Bent,'' ``A Cool, Dry Place,'' ``Rowing With the Wind.'' June 8:
``From the Earth to the Moon.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
