   CALDER SCULPTURE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ ``The Eagle'' has flown the coop. A
40-foot-tall orange steel sculpture by Alexander Calder that loomed
outside a downtown Fort Worth bank tower for a quarter-century
abruptly took flight on Sunday for parts unknown. The Dallas
company that bought the sculpture along with the Bank One tower
last fall said it sold the abstract artwork to finance building
improvements _ including the installation of fire sprinklers, which
the 36-story building lacks. By LAURA VOZZELLA. Story has moved in
``a'' general news category. &QL; 
