</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The warning signs are here _ a short, almost
nonexistent winter, an early, warm spring, less rainfall than
normal _ all indicators pointing to a meltdown summer. And then
there are all these new books: ``The Garden Room: Bringing Nature
Indoors'' by Timothy Mawson (Clarkson Potter, $24), ``Garden
Style'' (Better Homes and Garden Books, $34.95) and ``Gardenhouse:
Bringing the Outdoors In'' by Bonnie Trust Dahan (Chronicle Books,
$24.95). They too must be a sign that this summer will be a time of
legend, a season to hide from the heat, to retreat from the sun. By
