   AUCTION _ Auctions no longer revolve around estate jewelry,
autos and antiques. As more expensive houses are sold at auction,
the business itself becomes more competitive _ new players enter
the field. Story explains the business of home auctions and results
of recent auctions in metro Atlanta. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ROBINSON-HUMPHREY _ Robinson-Humphrey holds its 28th Annual
Institutional Conference at the Ritz-Carlton, Buckhead, beginning
with reception Sunday and continuing through Wednesday 14th. This
is a major event during which investors and journalists can hear
what the heads of companies are telling analysts about the
direction of their businesses. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   IMAC _ The computer-buying public hit a technological wall;
faster, more powerful computers don't sound as great as they once
did. Along comes the cute little iMac and suddenly technology is
becoming more about style. Story of how one computer has the
potential to start a revolution, in which we pick our technology by
design and color as much as by processor speed. iMac has changed
the playing field by introducing different ``flavors'' of
computers: Lime, blueberry, etc. (Kallenberg, Austin
American-Statesman). 35. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
