<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of April 13 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN _ Let the hire beware. Daily News columnist Ken
Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational behavior, answers
readers' questions on workplace ethics and relationships. (Will
move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   STAR-TIX (Los Angeles) _ It appears ``Star Wars'' fans won't
have to wait in line for days to see this spring's ``Episode 1:
Phantom Menace.'' George Lucas and 20th Century Fox appear to have
dropped their two-week-old request for same-day-only sales and will
allow theaters to sell tickets in advance. How far in advance and
how many tickets per customer are still to be determined. By Dave
McNary. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-INTERNET (Los Angeles) _ Rumors have emerged that Disney
will convert some of its Internet holdings into a separate publicly
traded company. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``f'' financial
news file.)
</P>
