<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-12 19:52 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5351 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI &LR;      04-12 0486
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Tuesday, April
13, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Veronica
Villarreal at (206) 448-8302.
</P>
<P>
   PULITZER-HORSEY (Seattle) _ Seattle Post-Intelligencer editorial
cartoonist David Horsey will Pulitzer.
</P>
<P>
   By Ellis E. Conklin. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   QUAKE-ANNIVERSARY (Seattle) _ At 11:55 a.m. on a Good Friday 50
years ago Tuesday, housewives around Puget Sound were tuned into
KVI radio's ``Queen for A Day.'' Seattle was savoring a win by its
beloved Rainiers baseball club over the Sacramento Solons the night
before. Outside in the fair, 58 degree weather, kids off school for
spring vacation were playing. A minute later, all that was
forgotten in the most destructive recorded earthquake to hit the
Pacific Northwest in this century.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Barber. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TEACHERS (Seattle) _ As teachers in Washington state campaign
for higher wages, Penny Pagels, a science teacher at Seattle's
Ballard High School, represents the educator who has spurned better
pay in private industry to come to the classroom.
</P>
<P>
   By John Iwasaki. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BANDS (Undated) _ If imitation is the sincerest form of
flattery, Tyler Lindsley and his band pay a whopping compliment to
The Cars. A Seattle quintet, Lindsley's band _ the Used Cars _ is
among hundreds of tribute bands that have found a niche mastering _
or at least mimicking _ another group's act.
</P>
<P>
   By Teresa Talerico. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   THEATER-ICEMAN (New York) _ Review of ``The Iceman Cometh'' with
Kevin Spacey.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) _ Seattle Mariners host Oakland.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-THIEL-COLUMN (Seattle) _ Sticker shock at Safeco Field, the
future home of the Mariners.
</P>
<P>
   By Art Thiel. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DRAFT-QBS _ The quarterback-starved NFL is about to get a
major infusion of talent at that pivotal position in this weekend's
draft. As many as five could go in the first round, putting this
year's group close to matching the total from the heralded Class of
'83.
</P>
<P>
   By Clare Farnsworth. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   GLF-DUFFER (Augusta, Ga.) _ First-person account of an average
joe golfer playing Augusta National. He got to duel the hallowed
links Monday.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Moore. (story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   THORNTON-OBIT (Seattle) _ Former Boeing chairman and chief
executive officer Thornton Arnold ``T'' Wilson, credited with
producing the Boeing 747, has died at his home in Palm Springs,
Calif.
</P>
<P>
   By Paul Shukovsky. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
