 Monday, April 12, 1999    
 Editors     
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service has filed or will file the following for
Tuesday. If you have questions, please call Susie McBee or Mark
Helm at 202-298-6920.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (EDs: Adding HORSEY-PULITZER)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all sluglines.)
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ Foreign ministers from NATO countries
gather in Brussels, Belgium, to demonstrate their unity as NATO war
planes continue to pound Yugoslavia. By CRAGG HINES.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-CLINTON (Barksdale Air Force Base, La.) _ President
Clinton thanks the pilots and air crews who have been taking part
in the NATO mission in Kosovo. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   NASA-RUSSIA (Houston) _ U.S. and Russian officials near an
agreement on the construction of an international space station. By
MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   HORSEY-PULITZER (New York) _ already filed _ David Horsey,
Seattle Post-Intelligencer editorial cartoonist, has won the 1999
Pulitzer Prize in Journalism for Editorial Cartooning. Winners of
the prize, one of the most prestigious awards in American
journalism, were announced Monday afternoon. The Post-Intelligencer
is one of 12 daily newspapers published by The Hearst Corporation.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
