<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THOSE ROLLICKING STATES OF THE NATION
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Here's why  &UR; Garrison Keillor &LR; , host of the St. Paul-based
radio show ``A Prairie Home Companion,'' is at war with Minnesota
Governor  &UR; Jesse Ventura &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   First, Keillor told Time magazine he thought the governor was
``a great big honking bullet-headed shovel-faced `mutha' who talks
in a steroid growl.'' Then he wrote a satiric novel, ``Me, by Jimmy
(Big Boy) Valente,'' which he published in three weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Ventura wasn't going to take that lying down, especially as he
was about to publish his own book _ ``I Ain't Got Time to Bleed'' _
about his rise to greatness. Ventura announced that he would kill
state funding for Minnesota Public Radio, which produces Keillor's
show.
</P>
<P>
   Keillor has responded with weekly criticism of Ventura, whom he
said has ``the IQ of a salad bar.'' He told the Los Angeles Times
that ``the governor owns Jet Skis and loves to get on them on a
quiet Sunday afternoon and ride the hell out of them. I'm the
person sitting on the porch of a cabin on shore, quietly wishing
the person making that infernal buzzing noise would hit a dock and
break a leg.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Maryland Secretary of Transportation  &UR; John Porcari &LR;  was
scheduled to introduce the main speaker, Maryland  &LR; Gov.  &UR; Parris &LR; 
 &UR; Glendening &LR; , at a public event last week. Pulling the text of his
remarks from a folder, Porcari began, ``Thank you, John, for that
introduction,'' and continued reading the whole of the governor's
prepared speech.
</P>
<P>
   This left the governor with the chore of making up something on
the spot, which he did.
</P>
<P>
   Later in the day, his office issued a staff decree, which was
quoted by the Washington Post: ``Effective immediately, the
governor's remarks, and only the governor's remarks, are to be
printed on canary yellow paper. ... Please be sure your bosses know
they should never read from the remarks on yellow paper.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Missouri state Representative  &UR; Sam Gaskill  &LR; has proposed a
bill, says Washington Monthly, that would require hospitals to
provide patients with ``dignity gowns'' that would cover them neck
to knee, all around.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NEAR AND FAR &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ How do you define optimism?  &UR; Hoyt Smith &LR;  saw a man taking the
Muni Metro inbound from Castro Street, carrying a large hot pizza
to his friends downtown.
</P>
<P>
   In other urban developments, shirts worn by staff members of the
San Francisco Convention and Visitors Bureau _ button-downs with
bureau patches _ are featured in the latest issue of the Lands' End
catalog, which is, in turn, cited in the latest issue of the
bureau's Cablegram.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not sure how many people are thinking about the next
vacation while perusing a Lands End catalog,'' said bureau manager
 &UR; Dayna Nelson &LR; , ``but when you see the page with the shirts you
can't help but think about San Francisco.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Andrei Andronnikov &LR; , who is the head of Mosfilm, the largest
film studio in Russia, dressed up as a knight and rode on horseback
to the residence of the American ambassador in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
   When he got there, reported the Sunday Times of London, he shot
arrows at the building, each of which had a note attached
protesting NATO air strikes in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ If you're tired of spending countless hours searching on the
Internet for pictures of naked celebrities, an on- &LR; line spammeister
is offering the Celebrity Nudes CD-ROM, which he says contains more
than 8,500 images. Among the stars offered in the buff: &UR; Faye
Resnick &LR; ,  &UR; Diane Sawyer &LR; ,  &UR; Debby Boone  &LR; and  &UR; Betty &LR; 
 &UR; White &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Michael Wiesenberg &LR; 's nomination for Strange Bumperfellows: A
company truck labeled ``Echo Systems Inc., Ob/Gyn Ultrasound'' bore
a bumper sticker for ``Mystery Spot, Santa Cruz.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Animal Times, the magazine of People for the Ethical Treatment
of Animals, urges consumers to buy only ``cruelty-free toilet
paper.''
</P>
<P>
   Conscience-stricken consumers should note that this doesn't
necessarily mean that animals are sacrificed (try not to picture
it) in the testing of ordinary toilet paper. It means that some
companies _ Procter &AMP; Gamble, for example _ use animals to test
other products.
</P>
<P>
   _ Actor  &UR; Benjamin Bratt &LR;  told InStyle magazine that the best
present he ever got was a pair of Gucci mules from his girlfriend,
 &UR; Julia Roberts &LR; . ``No one had ever given me shoes as a gift
before.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
