<P>
   CLINTON-CONTEMPT (Washington) _ Judge Webber Wright finds
President Clinton in civil contempt for his lies in the Paula Jones
civil deposition. She wrote: ``It is difficult to construe the
president's sworn statements ... as anything other than a willful
refusal to obey this court's discovery orders.'' The judge said,
``The record demonstrates by clear and convincing evidence that the
president responded to plaintiffs' questions by giving false,
misleading and evasive answers that were designed to obstruct the
judicial process.'' By John M. Broder.
</P>
