<P>
   MCDOUGAL-TRIAL (Little Rock, Ark.) _ A federal jury today
acquitted Susan H. McDougal of obstructing justice for her refusal
to testify before a grand jury about the Arkansas financial
dealings of President Clinton and his wife, Hillary Rodham Clinton.
But the jury, in its third day of deliberations, deadlocked on two
other counts of criminal contempt and the judge, George Howard Jr.,
declared a mistrial. Although the jury's action was a mixed result,
it amounted to a setback for Kenneth Starr, the independent counsel
for Whitewater matters who Ms. McDougal claimed was out to get
Clinton. By Neil A. Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   2-column hed.
</P>
