NATO warplanes bombed two bridges Monday morning over the Juzna
Morava River, one highway, one railway, a narrow structure of steel
girders painted a dull gray. The train, five cars pulled by a
bright red, white and blue engine, was on the bridge, and the
missile cut it in half. At least nine people were killed, said
police at the scene, and at least 16 others, badly injured, were
brought to a hospital in nearby Leskovac. By Steven Erlanger.
