A5512 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HILLARY-CLINTON-COX     04-12 0304
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HILLARY-CLINTON-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Hillary Clinton to dine in Wexler's honor
 &HT;    By Brian E. Crowley
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOCA RATON, Fla. _ U.S. Rep. Robert Wexler, who traveled the
national talk show circuit defending President Clinton during his
impeachment hearing and trial, is raising money for his reelection
campaign tonight with a dinner featuring first lady Hillary Rodham
Clinton.
</P>
<P>
   The $1,000 per person dinner is at the Boca Raton Resort and
Club.
</P>
<P>
   Wexler, a Boca Raton Democrat seeking a third term, was one of
the president's loudest supporters, although he said he was
bitterly disappointed about Clinton's affair with Monica Lewinsky.
</P>
<P>
   Prior to the dinner, Wexler and Mrs. Clinton will participate in
a Holocaust memorial program at the Jewish Federation of South Palm
Beach County.
</P>
<P>
   The Yom Hashoah ceremony, which began at sundown Monday and ends
at sundown today, remembers the millions of Jews killed during the
Holocaust.
</P>
<P>
   The dinner is a purely political event. Wexler has said that
instead of running for a third term he might run for the seat held
by U.S. Sen. Connie Mack, who is retiring. Wexler has indicated
that such a run is a long shot, but he wants to take a careful look
at the race. The front-runner for the Democratic nomination is
state Insurance Commissioner Bill Nelson.
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Clinton should find a receptive audience here, particularly
among former New Yorkers who are wondering whether she will run for
the U.S. Senate there.
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Clinton has said she is seriously considering a race for
the seat held by Democrat Daniel Patrick Moynihan who is retiring
after 24 years in the Senate.
</P>
<P>
   Brian E. Crowley writes for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm
Beach, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
