<P>
   (NYT18) ON THE GRAND TRUNK ROAD, India -- April 12, 1999 --
PAKISTAN-BUS-1, 4-12 -- On a bus running between New Delhi, India,
and Lahore, Pakistan - two countries that have fought three wars
since 1947 - some passengers sleep. ``Only time will tell whether
this bus will bring people together, but it is a good thing that it
has started,'' says Rafiq Sutarrya, an Indian plywood salesman
whose sentiments echoed those of his fellow travelers. (Celia W.
Dugger/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) NAZARETH, Israel -- April 12, 1999 -- NAZARETH-PLAZA,
4-12 -- Arab muslims during midday prayers in front of the Basilica
of the Annunciation, an elegant modern building that stands atop
the ruined walls of a 12th Century Crusader church. Local muslims
plan to build a mosque right next to the church. The resulting
fight pits the Muslim world against the Vatican - with Israel, an
interested party, in the unlikely role of gendarme. (Rina
Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo) *LITE
