   (NYT6) UNDATED -- April 12, 1999 -- SCI-DEFIBRILLATORS, 4-12 --
Portable defibrillators - which weigh about four to seven pounds
and are computerized to be easy enough for a child to learn to
operate - are making a major difference in cardiac survival rates.
More and more businesses and organizations are recognizing their
value. (Naum Kazhdan/New York Times Photo)
