Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center in New York. Cordon-Cardo is
a leader among researchers hoping to use molecular pathology to
transform the treatment of many cancers, increasing patients'
chances of cure in some cases and avoiding unnecessary treatment in
others. (Don Hogan Charles/New York Times Photo)
